This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of video super-resolution, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of a recurrent encoder-decoder module also suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the cs.CV sub-category. 

The paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as video super-resolution is a multimedia task that involves processing and enhancing video content. 

The use of iterative refinement and back-projection techniques suggests a focus on optimization and machine learning, which could place the paper in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of enhancing video content, which is a common task in computer graphics.
